The past three days have been an incredible experience for me, as I had the privilege of accompanying a Tamil stand-up comedian from my community both as a comedy show producer and a supporter. It fills me with immense pride to have been a part of this journey and to witness this historic moment alongside him and the audience. Being the first Tamil stand-up comedian to perform at the renowned APOLLO THEATER in Paris and Comedyhaus in Zurich has been an absolute honor. I want to express my heartfelt gratitude to the exceptionally talented artist, Sunthar V, the enthusiastic audience, the amazing venues, and everyone involved in making this project a success 🙏🏽✨

Made history in France & Switzerland. 👉🏾👈🏾. I have so much to say but, here’s what others are saying about #AvanaNee. Merci beaucoup Paris et Zurich! I can’t wait to be back. 💛❤️🌈

Fresh off his sold out tour in Canada, @suntharv is finally coming to NEW YORK CITY with his show “Avana Nee?” 🎙️

“Avana Nee?” is an engaging and thought-provoking comedy show that delves into the intricacies of identity and self- discovery. With humour and authenticity, Sunthar explores the intersection of being Tamil, queer, and child of refugees, asking the audience, "Is that really you?"

With sold out shows in 🇬🇧 London, 🇫🇷 Paris 🇨🇭Zurich, and across 🇨🇦 Canada, we’re super excited to bring Sunthar to the 🇺🇸 US and to our Tamil community here in 🗽 NYC!

Tickets are now on live @ suntharv.com or the link in the bio ⬆️

Amsterdam! 🤩We’re delighted to announce that the hilarious @suntharv will be bringing his comedy special “Avana Nee?” to @barpekky on 8th December (Friday) at 18:30. Tickets on sale now from link in bio! 🎟 

“Avana Nee?” by Sunthar V is an engaging and thought-provoking comedy show that delves into the intricacies of identity and self- discovery. With humour and authenticity, Sunthar explores the intersection of being Tamil, queer, and child of refugees, asking the audience, "Is that really you?"

Through hilarious anecdotes and heartfelt moments, Sunthar navigates the complexities of growing up in the Western world, while staying true to his Tamil roots and grappling with the influence of Tamil pop culture.

Prepare to be entertained and enlightened as Sunthar takes you on a captivating journey of self-reflection, challenging societal norms, and celebrating the beauty of embracing one's true self.

This show will feature @theramarangistory as the opening act. 

A @localtouristcomedy production! 🥳

A massive shout out and thanks to our media team @akmedia.to for covering the shows’ best memories so well👏🏽

Through hilarious anecdotes and heartfelt moments, Sunthar navigates the complexities of growing up in the Western world, while staying true to his Tamil roots and grappling with the influence of Tamil pop culture.

Prepare to be entertained and enlightened as Sunthar takes you on a captivating journey of self-reflection, challenging societal norms, and celebrating the beauty of embracing one's true self.

been 2 years since I lost my “dream” 6-figure job at a company (rhymes with iceberg) that created a racist group chat about me before i even started 😂 (more on that in my tell-all special one day ☕️) and 1 year since I went full time with comedy. I’ve made less than 20% of what I would have made in the corporate roles I’m qualified for. I’ve lived out of a bag and sleeping on couches of the realest friends when I’m not in my parents basement. In many ways I’m my own start up. Everything is learning (both in business and on stage). In between shows and bookings I’ve felt a depression and loneliness like never before. But, it’s all part of the grind(r). Next week I’m wrapping up a crazy year of #AvanaNee in Amsterdam and ramping up for some of my biggest shows next year. Anyway, just want to thank you all for riding with me (and my cue cards) from city to city, stage to stage, as I figure out how to make the real dream work for me. hope to see more of you in 2024. Please just help me by signing up for pre-sales on my website! First stop, Scarborough. More history to be made. 💛❤️🌈
